Inter-religious conference‘Prophet Muhammad – the pinnacle of Humanity’, an inter-religious conference organised by Jamaat-e-Islami Hind, Bengaluru Metro, will be held on January 30. Shivarudra Swami of Belimatha Mahasmathana, the former Chief Justice of India M.N. Venkatachaliah, Archbishop of Bengaluru Bernard Moras, litterateur Hampa Nagarajaiah, head priest of Ulsoor grudwara Giani Baldev Singh, and manager of Shanthi Prakashana, Mangaluru, Mohammed Kunhi are expected to participate. Moulana Syed Jalaluddin Umri, national president of Jamaat-e-Islami Hind, will deliver the keynote address. The event will be held at Ambedkar Bhavan on Millers Road from 7 p.m.